  "prompt": "Does water exist on mars?",
  "response": "Yes, water exists on Mars. Scientists have found evidence of water ice at the poles and below the surface. Additionally, data from various missions, such as those by the Mars Reconnaissance Orbiter and Curiosity Rover, have revealed signs of liquid water in the form of seasonal flows and ancient riverbeds and lakebeds, suggesting that water was once more abundant on the planet. However, liquid water is not stable on the surface of Mars under current conditions due to low atmospheric pressure and temperature, but the presence of water ice indicates that water is available in some form.",
